[b]MTF WaveTrend Opportunity Hunter[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

A multi-timeframe confluence pane built around WaveTrend. Instead of reducing MTF analysis to a one-bar signal label, it makes confluence visible over time: a net confluence histogram plus four heat ribbons — one per scoring layer — show at every bar why a signal fired, or which layer is currently holding one back.

Signals use a deliberately slim gate of three conditions. Quality does not block signals — it grades them A or B, so you decide what to skip.

[b]The three-condition gate[/b]

[list=1]
[*][b]Regime bias[/b] — the Regime timeframe (default: Daily) must show a directional regime: WaveTrend trend, EMA50/200 alignment, ADX strength. Scored 0–100, must pass the configured minimum.
[*][b]Setup pullback[/b] — the Setup timeframe (default: 4H) must offer location: price pulled back toward the JMA and WaveTrend near an extreme. Scored 0–100, must pass the configured minimum.
[*][b]Trigger[/b] — a WaveTrend cross on the Trigger timeframe (default: 1H). An event, not a threshold.
[/list]

[b]Reading the pane[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Histogram[/b] — net confluence (long minus short final score, −100…+100), green above zero, red below, with ±60 reference lines
[*][b]Heat ribbons[/b] — Regime / Opportunity / Timing / Quality as color strips: green = long-side dominance, red = short-side, gray = neutral
[*][b]Noise ribbon[/b] — Shannon sign-entropy of the trigger timeframe, percentile-ranked so it self-calibrates per instrument: green = unusually clean tape, orange = unusually noisy
[*]Three ribbons green and Timing gray = ARMED — only the trigger cross is missing
[*]Regime ribbon flipping while in a trade = exit warning likely ahead
[/list]

[b]Confluence Rotation Map[/b]

A quadrant inset (inspired by Relative Rotation Graphs) right of the last bar: x = net confluence, y = confluence momentum. The curved trail shows the recent path; the dot shows the current state — LEADING (confluence strong and rising), WEAKENING (strong but stalling), LAGGING, IMPROVING (weak but building). A rotation through IMPROVING toward LEADING is the classic early-entry pattern.

[b]Ultimate Smoother core[/b]

Optionally (default on) the EMA core of WaveTrend is replaced by John Ehlers' Ultimate Smoother (TASC 04/2024) — a filter with zero lag in its passband. Crosses arrive earlier at the same length, without the whipsaw of simply shortening the EMA.

[b]On the price chart[/b]

[list]
[*]LONG A / LONG B / SHORT A / SHORT B entry labels (A = Quality score passes the Grade A threshold)
[*]Persistent risk zone (entry to stop, red) and first-target zone (entry to TP1, green), with TP2/TP3 lines — extended while the trade is active, frozen on exit warning
[*]Orange × exit warnings — only during an active trade, when trend health drops or WaveTrend crosses back
[/list]

[b]Dashboard[/b]

Per-side Long/Short columns with all four layer scores, gate-pass coloring, the live WT-cross state, and a status row: SIGNAL / ARMED (gates pass, waiting for trigger) / REGIME / PULLBACK / OFF.

[b]Alerts[/b]

[list]
[*]Long / Short signal
[*]Long / Short Grade A signal
[*]Long / Short exit warning
[/list]

